T* () Tj
T* (Use this guide to run Mackey Hall video and audio for a meeting, class, presentation, or) Tj
T* (event. If you are not sure where to start, follow the quick start checklist first, then open) Tj
T* (the guide for the specific equipment you need.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Quick Start) Tj
T* (1. Turn on the sound system if you need microphones, computer audio, or Bluetooth audio.) Tj
T* (2. Lower the projector screen if the projector will be used.) Tj
T* (3. Turn on the projector or rear TV.) Tj
T* (4. Connect your device and select the matching video input.) Tj
T* (5. Use the iPad audio controls to choose the right preset and unmute the channels you need.) Tj
T* (6. Test both picture and sound before the event begins.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Choose What You Need) Tj
T* (| Need | Start Here |) Tj
T* (| --- | --- |) Tj
