T* (This guide explains how to lower the projector screen in Mackey Hall.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (If you need the reverse process, see Retracting Projector Screen.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Locate the Screen Control) Tj
T* (The projector screen control switch is on the south wall, to the right of the windows.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Image: Windows on South Wall) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Lower the Screen) Tj
T* (1. Press the lower half of the screen control switch fully in.) Tj
T* (2. The switch is a maintained toggle, so it will stay in the selected position.) Tj
T* (3. Wait while the screen lowers.) Tj
T* (4. The screen will stop automatically at its lowest position.) Tj
T* (5. Toggle the switch back to the neutral \(center\) position after the screen is fully) Tj
T* (lowered.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Image: Projector Switch in Down Position) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
