(Start Pairing Mode \(Two Ways\)) Tj
T* (Method 1: From the Audio Page) Tj
T* (1. On the wall touchscreen Homepage, press Audio.) Tj
T* (Image: Control Screen Homepage) Tj
T* (2. On the Audio page, press Bluetooth Pair.) Tj
T* (Image: Audio Page) Tj
T* (3. Wait a few seconds for pairing mode to activate.) Tj
T* (4. If room speakers are unmuted, you should hear a beep when pairing mode starts.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Method 2: From Audio Levels -> Computer + Bluetooth Inputs) Tj
T* (1. On Select a Preset, choose Computer + Bluetooth Inputs.) Tj
T* (2. On that page, press Bluetooth Pairing.) Tj
T* (3. Wait a few seconds for pairing mode to activate.) Tj
T* (4. If room speakers are unmuted, you should hear a beep when pairing mode starts.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Connect Your Device) Tj
T* (1. On your phone, tablet, or computer, open Bluetooth settings.) Tj
T* (2. Select DN-200BR from available devices.) Tj
T* (3. Confirm the device shows as connected.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Route Bluetooth Audio to Speakers) Tj
T* (1. On the wall touchscreen Audio page, press Audio Levels.) Tj
T* (2. On Select a Preset, choose Computer + Bluetooth Inputs.) Tj
T* (3. In that preset, find the Bluetooth channel card.) Tj
T* (4. If Muted is red, press it once to unmute.) Tj
T* (5. Start playback and adjust Bluetooth level with +1%, -1%, or the slider.) Tj
T* (6. Use the Speakers card on the right \(Master Output\) for overall room output level.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Image: Computer and Bluetooth Controls) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Notes) Tj
T* (- Pairing is for playback devices only.) Tj
T* (- If pairing fails, press Bluetooth Pair again and retry from Bluetooth settings.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (\\newpage) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Connecting and Using Microphones) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (This guide explains how to set up and use microphones in Mackey Hall with the wall) Tj
T* (touchscreen audio controls.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Before You Start) Tj
T* (1. Make sure the sound system is on. If needed, see Turning the Sound System On.) Tj
T* (2. Open the wall touchscreen audio controls and select the correct preset. If needed, see) Tj
T* (Using Audio Controls.) Tj
T* (3. Use Pulpit Wired Mics for pulpit channels Pulpit 1 and Pulpit 2.) Tj
ET
endstream
